1
00:00:00,828 --> 00:00:05,203
I'm not just saying it, nor am I joking.

2
00:00:05,203 --> 00:00:07,932
I'm asking you to be my girlfriend again.

3
00:00:07,932 --> 00:00:10,601
I want to start over with you.

4
00:00:12,121 --> 00:00:13,671
Hyeon Ho, I—

5
00:00:13,671 --> 00:00:15,932
I'll do better.

6
00:00:17,126 --> 00:00:20,020
I will never make you cry again. I promise.

7
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:25,317
What?

8
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:28,202
Do you know how I feel right now?

9
00:00:34,309 --> 00:00:35,952
No.

10
00:00:39,465 --> 00:00:41,900
Thank you for helping me yesterday and today,

11
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,768
but...

12
00:00:45,137 --> 00:00:47,881
I don't want to get back together with you.

13
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,566
I'm sorry.

14
00:01:15,676 --> 00:01:20,500
[Best Mistake 3]

15
00:01:28,597 --> 00:01:29,464
What?

16
00:01:29,489 --> 00:01:32,817
You guys are in a relationship but don't talk about stuff like that?

17
00:01:32,817 --> 00:01:33,852
Why didn't you tell me?

18
00:01:33,852 --> 00:01:35,729
Is that how much trust you have in me?

19
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:38,680
You haven't been as miserable as I am.

20
00:01:47,332 --> 00:01:52,390
[Hyeon Ho's cooking competition: Wednesday, October 20, 2021, All Day Long Event]

21
00:01:53,605 --> 00:01:57,110
It's not far off now.

22
00:01:57,110 --> 00:01:59,836
I should stay strong.

23
00:02:15,786 --> 00:02:17,995
Date me.

24
00:02:17,995 --> 00:02:19,806
What?

25
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:22,151
Let's date.

26
00:02:22,151 --> 00:02:24,277
Let's start over.

27
00:02:38,417 --> 00:02:41,577
What's going on? Why the long face?

28
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:45,239
Porridge?

29
00:02:45,239 --> 00:02:46,825
Are you sick?

30
00:02:46,825 --> 00:02:49,085
No.

31
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:52,046
Then is this for me?

32
00:02:52,906 --> 00:02:54,682
It's seaweed porridge.

33
00:02:54,682 --> 00:02:57,743
You're the best.

34
00:02:57,743 --> 00:03:00,560
How did you know I liked this?

35
00:03:07,404 --> 00:03:09,046
What the...

36
00:03:09,046 --> 00:03:11,307
Why is it so cold?

37
00:03:12,201 --> 00:03:14,577
When did you buy this?

38
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:20,091
Has it gone bad?

39
00:03:20,091 --> 00:03:22,202
I bought it today.

40
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:25,205
You can take it home and warm it up.

41
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:26,298
No.

42
00:03:26,298 --> 00:03:28,408
It wouldn't taste as good.

43
00:03:28,408 --> 00:03:31,116
Porridge is best served hot off the stove. Okay?

44
00:03:31,116 --> 00:03:33,346
Food is all about timing.

45
00:03:33,346 --> 00:03:35,597
Don't you know the famous phrase?

46
00:03:35,597 --> 00:03:38,520
You mean, "Love is all about timing."

47
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,756
I know that. "Love is all about timing."

48
00:03:44,756 --> 00:03:49,801
No matter how hard you love, it's futile if you miss the timing.

49
00:03:49,801 --> 00:03:51,681
That's what it means, right?

50
00:03:51,681 --> 00:03:53,533
Right.

51
00:03:55,077 --> 00:03:58,179
I shouldn't miss the timing.

52
00:03:58,179 --> 00:03:59,790
Definitely.

53
00:03:59,790 --> 00:04:02,584
Food and love are the same.

54
00:04:02,584 --> 00:04:05,053
If you miss the timing,

55
00:04:05,896 --> 00:04:08,331
it'll become cold like this porridge.

56
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:13,394
Well, this porridge is actually not so bad.

57
00:04:22,087 --> 00:04:23,620
[2022 College Scholastic Ability Test October Mock Exam]

58
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:27,940
[Math]

59
00:04:47,354 --> 00:04:49,414
That won't help you get better grades.

60
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:51,948
What? What are you doing here?

61
00:04:51,948 --> 00:04:54,819
When did you come?

62
00:04:55,512 --> 00:04:57,980
You blew it, like getting in the 4th level group.

63
00:05:02,102 --> 00:05:04,070
Hey! What about you?

64
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:05,938
You probably did as bad as I.

65
00:05:05,938 --> 00:05:07,874
How dare you say that?

66
00:05:09,192 --> 00:05:12,630
Ah Hun's score went up.
[Math: 73]

67
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:19,969
Really?

68
00:05:19,969 --> 00:05:22,888
Ah Hun is on another level.

69
00:05:22,888 --> 00:05:24,741
Better level!

70
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:28,119
Bye.

71
00:05:28,144 --> 00:05:29,712
Ah Hun has to go to show this to my mom.

72
00:05:29,712 --> 00:05:31,505
See you in class!

73
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:46,820
[Math: 52]

74
00:06:03,413 --> 00:06:05,432
Is he still in class?

75
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:16,793
Hi, Choi—

76
00:06:16,818 --> 00:06:18,078
Sorry, I'm in the middle of training.

77
00:06:18,078 --> 00:06:19,970
I'll call you later.

78
00:06:26,828 --> 00:06:29,030
Everyone is busy.

79
00:06:39,552 --> 00:06:43,077
Photo Club Moment members!

80
00:06:43,077 --> 00:06:45,472
Design students from Hwayang College are holding an exhibition.

81
00:06:45,472 --> 00:06:47,790
Message us if you want to come!

82
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:50,026
I got stressed out trying to write my essay so I came to drink!

83
00:06:50,026 --> 00:06:53,254
This is #K-CollegeLife.

84
00:06:53,254 --> 00:06:57,209
You want to transfer to another university, but don't know how to spell "TOEIC." Lol.

85
00:07:13,725 --> 00:07:15,401
Bye!

86
00:07:16,344 --> 00:07:18,754
[Jiseong: Missed call, 15 minutes ago]

87
00:07:18,754 --> 00:07:21,257
I wonder why he called me.

88
00:07:21,257 --> 00:07:23,384
The number you are calling is turned off.

89
00:07:23,384 --> 00:07:26,765
Your call will be forwarded to voicemail after the beep.

90
00:07:26,765 --> 00:07:29,899
Why is it turned off?

91
00:07:30,642 --> 00:07:33,135
He is probably not in class.

92
00:07:40,527 --> 00:07:43,755
Has anyone contacted Ji Seong today?

93
00:07:43,755 --> 00:07:45,423
He called me, but I missed it.

94
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:47,300
I couldn't answer because I was in class.

95
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,969
I answered,

96
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:51,504
but I was training, so I told him I'd call back.

97
00:07:51,504 --> 00:07:53,697
Oh?

98
00:07:53,697 --> 00:07:56,116
He called me, too.

99
00:07:56,116 --> 00:07:57,168
Me, too.

100
00:07:57,168 --> 00:07:59,537
He must've called all of us.

101
00:07:59,537 --> 00:08:01,272
I guess so.

102
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:03,641
Then no one answered his call?

103
00:08:03,641 --> 00:08:05,335
And no one has seen him today?

104
00:08:05,335 --> 00:08:08,829
Ah Hun saw him briefly earlier.

105
00:08:08,829 --> 00:08:12,265
He was checking his mock exam results in front of the convenience store.

106
00:08:12,265 --> 00:08:13,610
Mock exam?

107
00:08:13,610 --> 00:08:14,536
Yes.

108
00:08:14,536 --> 00:08:18,945
He was depressed because he didn't do as well as he'd hoped.

109
00:08:20,525 --> 00:08:22,035
I think Ji Seong disappeared.

110
00:08:22,035 --> 00:08:23,928
What?

111
00:08:26,056 --> 00:08:27,715
Come here.

112
00:08:28,491 --> 00:08:30,218
What happened?

113
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:32,094
I don't know.

114
00:08:33,129 --> 00:08:35,381
Where could he be?

115
00:08:39,402 --> 00:08:40,337
Was it there?

116
00:08:40,337 --> 00:08:42,146
Yes, that's the convenience store.

117
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:44,360
- Let's go.
- Yes.

118
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:50,779
Where is he?

119
00:08:54,876 --> 00:08:56,952
Is he not inside?

120
00:09:00,198 --> 00:09:02,558
Are you sure you saw him here?

121
00:09:08,170 --> 00:09:12,310
[Study Academy]

122
00:09:13,662 --> 00:09:14,754
Where is Ji Seong?

123
00:09:14,754 --> 00:09:16,498
They said he left right after the mock exam.

124
00:09:16,498 --> 00:09:18,999
There were no classes after that.

125
00:09:19,876 --> 00:09:24,277
He usually goes straight home from the academy. Where did he go?

126
00:09:24,277 --> 00:09:26,757
You don't have any idea where he could be?

127
00:09:26,757 --> 00:09:27,517
I'm hungry.

128
00:09:27,517 --> 00:09:29,009
Let's go to eat tteokbokki.

129
00:09:29,009 --> 00:09:29,944
Tteokbokki cooking on the table?

130
00:09:29,944 --> 00:09:31,553
Okay.

131
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:36,717
That time...

132
00:09:38,061 --> 00:09:40,421
Life was better in school.

133
00:09:40,421 --> 00:09:43,157
It was great except for all the studying.

134
00:09:43,157 --> 00:09:47,651
Ji Seong will go to college with you guys no matter what.

135
00:09:47,651 --> 00:09:49,155
Ji Seong won't retake the CSAT for the third time.

136
00:09:49,155 --> 00:09:51,515
Never.

137
00:09:51,515 --> 00:09:53,609
I think I know.

138
00:09:53,609 --> 00:09:57,353
I think I know where Ji Seong is.

139
00:09:57,353 --> 00:09:58,972
Hey!

140
00:10:04,212 --> 00:10:05,864
Why did you bring us to the school all of a sudden?

141
00:10:05,864 --> 00:10:07,132
Do you think Ji Seong is here?

142
00:10:07,132 --> 00:10:08,550
It's a bit random.

143
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:11,884
No. I'm sure he's here.

144
00:10:17,726 --> 00:10:19,351
Teacher!

145
00:10:19,351 --> 00:10:21,955
What are you graduates doing here?

146
00:10:21,955 --> 00:10:23,381
Hi.

147
00:10:23,381 --> 00:10:24,524
Hi.

148
00:10:24,524 --> 00:10:26,801
Are you having a reunion?

149
00:10:26,801 --> 00:10:28,486
No, we're—

150
00:10:28,486 --> 00:10:31,372
This is not your school anymore.

151
00:10:31,372 --> 00:10:35,467
Take Jeong Ji Seong out of the classroom and leave.

152
00:10:35,467 --> 00:10:36,519
Classroom?

153
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:38,004
Which classroom?

154
00:10:38,004 --> 00:10:41,510
Twelfth grade room number 7, of course.

155
00:10:49,115 --> 00:10:50,658
Teacher! Thank you.

156
00:10:50,658 --> 00:10:53,178
We'll bring the whole class later to see you.

157
00:10:53,178 --> 00:10:54,979
Thank you!

158
00:10:58,366 --> 00:11:00,159
Those kids...

159
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:02,395
I told them to leave and they really left.

160
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:05,614
They never used to listen to me.

161
00:11:20,488 --> 00:11:22,498
Jeong Ji Seong.

162
00:11:27,721 --> 00:11:30,414
What are you guys doing here?

163
00:11:31,007 --> 00:11:34,760
We were looking for you.

164
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,120
Ji Seong?

165
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,605
Why were you looking for Ji Seong?

166
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,109
Hyung Ji Seong.

167
00:11:41,109 --> 00:11:45,387
I'm sorry for boasting about my mock exam scores.

168
00:11:46,881 --> 00:11:51,008
The truth is I guessed a few of them,

169
00:11:51,008 --> 00:11:53,754
so I didn't do better than you.

170
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:55,964
Hyung!

171
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,001
Hey!

172
00:11:58,001 --> 00:12:00,586
Don't do that.

173
00:12:00,586 --> 00:12:05,163
You might end up taking the CSAT again like me.

174
00:12:07,210 --> 00:12:10,030
Don't try to take the CSAT again.

175
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:14,889
You get really lonely when everyone else has gone to college.

176
00:12:14,889 --> 00:12:19,002
Hey, you're not alone.

177
00:12:19,002 --> 00:12:21,324
We all care about you.

178
00:12:21,324 --> 00:12:22,825
Exactly.

179
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:25,895
Pass the exam so we can hang out together.

180
00:12:25,895 --> 00:12:28,600
I'm sick of hanging out with Seo Ju Ho alone.

181
00:12:39,642 --> 00:12:44,110
Wang Ying Ling likes Ji Seong, too.

182
00:12:45,039 --> 00:12:47,123
What?

183
00:12:47,123 --> 00:12:49,159
Wang Ying Ling?

184
00:12:50,195 --> 00:12:53,746
That's so out of the blue, a love confession?

185
00:12:54,424 --> 00:12:58,493
Well, it's about time.

186
00:12:58,493 --> 00:13:00,138
[Ji Seong's CSAT day, Friday, December 3rd]

187
00:13:00,138 --> 00:13:01,856
I marked the date on my calendar.

188
00:13:01,856 --> 00:13:06,558
Wang Ying Ling has been thinking about you and rooting for you every day.

189
00:13:07,687 --> 00:13:10,900
So stay strong.

190
00:13:13,576 --> 00:13:15,769
Ah Ra.

191
00:13:20,183 --> 00:13:21,859
Thank you.

192
00:13:21,859 --> 00:13:26,585
Ji Seong will study really hard.

193
00:13:31,686 --> 00:13:37,562
So Ji Seong and Ah Hun, what scores did you get?

194
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,614
Well...

195
00:13:45,850 --> 00:13:48,435
Give me your exam papers.

196
00:13:48,435 --> 00:13:50,704
My exam papers...

197
00:13:52,882 --> 00:13:54,158
Ah Hun.

198
00:13:54,158 --> 00:13:58,129
Where are the exam papers?

199
00:13:59,806 --> 00:14:01,007
Well...

200
00:14:01,032 --> 00:14:03,208
The exam papers are...

201
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:09,549
- Sorry!
- Sorry!

202
00:14:11,609 --> 00:14:15,352
Hey! Where are you going?

203
00:14:21,895 --> 00:14:26,155
I'm exhausted from running around all day looking for Jeong Ji Seong.

204
00:14:26,155 --> 00:14:27,416
Are you okay?

205
00:14:27,416 --> 00:14:30,401
I mean, why didn't he answer his phone?

206
00:14:30,401 --> 00:14:31,896
The battery must've run out.

207
00:14:31,896 --> 00:14:34,657
He should've charged it.

208
00:14:34,657 --> 00:14:38,690
We wouldn't have worried so much if he had answered his phone.

209
00:14:39,817 --> 00:14:43,830
I hate it the most when people don't answer my calls.

210
00:15:02,927 --> 00:15:05,245
That's pretty. What is the name of that color?

211
00:15:05,245 --> 00:15:07,347
Mauve pink.

212
00:15:10,376 --> 00:15:12,561
Do you even know what it is?

213
00:15:13,271 --> 00:15:15,222
I might.

214
00:15:15,222 --> 00:15:17,257
Don't be so mean.

215
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:22,570
Oh right. Hold on.

216
00:15:30,121 --> 00:15:31,873
Things Seol hates.

217
00:15:31,873 --> 00:15:33,191
Being impolite.

218
00:15:33,191 --> 00:15:34,584
Swearing.

219
00:15:34,584 --> 00:15:36,377
Being nice to everyone.

220
00:15:36,377 --> 00:15:38,830
Hanging up on her.

221
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:49,089
Things that Seol thinks are cute.

222
00:15:49,089 --> 00:15:51,400
Things that Seol likes.

223
00:15:52,118 --> 00:15:53,811
Foods that Seol enjoys.

224
00:15:53,811 --> 00:15:55,946
Foods that Seol can't eat.

225
00:15:58,424 --> 00:15:59,792
Things I want to do when I go back to Korea:
[1. Go to a cafe together.]

226
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,377
2. Go to an amusement park in school uniforms.

227
00:16:01,401 --> 00:16:02,910
[3. Take a walk in the park.]
[4. Buy her a lipstick.]

228
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:04,340
[5. Go to an exhibition together.]

229
00:16:06,758 --> 00:16:10,000
I miss her so, so much.

230
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:28,821
Seol, it's your favorite

231
00:16:28,846 --> 00:16:30,714
chocolate cake.

232
00:16:31,599 --> 00:16:34,840
This is today's one-sided love.

233
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,900
Don't do anything else.

234
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:52,486
What?

235
00:16:56,399 --> 00:17:00,440
Stop your one-sided love.

236
00:17:03,114 --> 00:17:05,457
What do you mean?

237
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:38,266
The festival is coming up.

238
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:39,859
I wonder what our department will do.

239
00:17:39,859 --> 00:17:41,768
An escape room.

240
00:17:42,736 --> 00:17:44,296
Unni Se Hui.

241
00:17:44,296 --> 00:17:46,315
We decided we're going to do an escape room.

242
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:47,933
Here.

243
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:54,181
Oh, an escape room.
[Escape room booth]

244
00:17:54,932 --> 00:17:57,076
We did a survey

245
00:17:57,076 --> 00:18:00,287
and escape room receive the most votes.

246
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,359
Unni Se Hui,

247
00:18:07,403 --> 00:18:10,563
I'm sorry about the other day.

248
00:18:10,563 --> 00:18:14,575
I suspected you without checking properly.

249
00:18:14,575 --> 00:18:17,210
I'm so sorry.

250
00:18:17,210 --> 00:18:21,531
It's fine. You were shocked and flustered.

251
00:18:21,531 --> 00:18:24,377
Don't worry about it. I've moved on.

252
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,239
Unni Se Hui...

253
00:18:26,239 --> 00:18:30,023
I mean it. I'm busy thinking about the festival.

254
00:18:30,023 --> 00:18:33,935
I'm the representative for the sophomore, so I'm in charge of building the set.

255
00:18:33,935 --> 00:18:36,115
But it's quite big.

256
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,125
We're short-handed.

257
00:18:38,125 --> 00:18:40,077
Yeon Du, I was wondering...

258
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:41,579
I'll help you.

259
00:18:41,579 --> 00:18:42,663
What?

260
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:44,815
I feel terrible.

261
00:18:44,815 --> 00:18:48,017
I want to help you to make up for it.

262
00:18:49,111 --> 00:18:52,656
So you'll help me?

263
00:18:52,656 --> 00:18:53,916
Of course.

264
00:18:53,916 --> 00:18:56,551
I think it'll be fun.

265
00:18:57,428 --> 00:18:59,396
You can look forward to it.

266
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:05,377
It'll be a lot of fun.

267
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,130
♫ It spreads hotter ♫

268
00:19:24,130 --> 00:19:25,982
If you're free, would you like to come with me?

269
00:19:25,982 --> 00:19:27,024
Yes.

270
00:19:27,024 --> 00:19:30,176
Jin Se Hui. Let's talk briefly.

271
00:19:30,176 --> 00:19:32,563
I don't know what "we" are.

272
00:19:32,563 --> 00:19:36,598
Are you close enough to help each other?

273
00:19:36,598 --> 00:19:37,968
Do you want to use me again?

274
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:38,803
Yes.

275
00:19:38,803 --> 00:19:40,679
"Yes?"

276
00:19:41,497 --> 00:19:42,690
It's been a while.

277
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:43,530
